<node CREATED="1293529423053" ID="ID_587897083" MODIFIED="1293529426249" TEXT="No daylight savings time occurs in UTC, making it a useful timezone to perform date arithmetic without worrying about the confusion and ambiguities caused by daylight savings time transitions, your country changing its timezone, or mobile computers that move roam through multiple timezones.">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1273546089010" ID="ID_1837789286" MODIFIED="1275452060988" TEXT="Timestamp &#x6c92;&#x6709; Time Zone &#x4e4b;&#x5206;, &#x5168;&#x4e16;&#x754c;&#x540c;&#x4e00;&#x6642;&#x523b;&#x7684; Timestamp &#x90fd;&#x662f;&#x4e00;&#x6a23;&#x7684;"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1281738739909" ID="ID_1797117989" MODIFIED="1281738744431" POSITION="right" TEXT="Programming">
<node CREATED="1281738744754" ID="ID_1459518071" MODIFIED="1281738745596" TEXT="Java"/>
<node CREATED="1281738745805" ID="ID_810515850" MODIFIED="1281738748920" TEXT="Python">
<node CREATED="1273462494384" ID="ID_1238432191" LINK="http://docs.python.org/library/datetime.html" MODIFIED="1290663042714" TEXT="datetime (STD 2.3+)">
<node CREATED="1290663136012" ID="ID_1332875518" MODIFIED="1290663138047" TEXT="Overview">
<node CREATED="1290663253982" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1980443906" MODIFIED="1290663271075" TEXT="The `datetime` module supplies classes for manipulating dates and times in both simple and complex ways.">
<node CREATED="1290663266196" ID="ID_1854203726" MODIFIED="1290663355147" TEXT="While date and time arithmetic is supported, the focus of the implementation is on efficient member extraction for output formatting and manipulation.">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1290663271704" ID="ID_858084955" MODIFIED="1290738488402" TEXT="For related functionality, see also the `time` and `calendar` modules."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1290663382845" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1696560487" MODIFIED="1290663789015" TEXT="There are two kinds of date and time objects: &#x201c;naive&#x201d; and &#x201c;aware&#x201d;.">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
<node CREATED="1290663455262" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_68246502" MODIFIED="1290663510864" TEXT="This distinction refers to whether the object has any notion of time zone, daylight saving time, or other kind of algorithmic or political &apos;&apos;time adjustment&apos;&apos;.">
<node CREATED="1290664492394" ID="ID_226488328" MODIFIED="1290738567639" TEXT="Objects of the `date` type are always naive. (&#x56e0;&#x70ba;&#x6642;&#x5dee;&#x4e0d;&#x6703;&#x5dee;&#x5230; 1 &#x5929;&#x4ee5;&#x4e0a;?)">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1290664598468" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1354798723" MODIFIED="1290664743165" TEXT="An object `d` of type `time` or `datetime` may be naive or aware.">
<node CREATED="1290664743552" ID="ID_1302495783" MODIFIED="1290664761669" TEXT="`d` is aware if `d.tzinfo` is not `None` and `d.tzinfo.utcoffset(d)` does not return `None`."/>
<node CREATED="1290664762003" ID="ID_1676796947" MODIFIED="1290664762379" TEXT="If `d.tzinfo` is `None`, or if `d.tzinfo` is not `None` but `d.tzinfo.utcoffset(d)` returns `None`, `d` is naive."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1290664612516" ID="ID_1022348963" MODIFIED="1290664612516" TEXT="The distinction between naive and aware doesn&#x2019;t apply to `timedelta` objects."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1290663511175" ID="ID_1868282992" MODIFIED="1293603776778" TEXT="Whether a naive `datetime` object represents Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), local time, or time in some other timezone is purely up to the program, just like it&#x2019;s up to the program whether a particular number represents metres, miles, or mass.">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
<icon BUILTIN="bookmark"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1290663540907" ID="ID_1958947617" MODIFIED="1290663541255" TEXT="Naive `datetime` objects are easy to understand and to work with, at the cost of ignoring some aspects of reality."/>
<node CREATED="1290663662113" ID="ID_555002356" MODIFIED="1293603836608" TEXT="For applications requiring more, `datetime` and `time` objects have an optional time zone information member, `tzinfo`, that can contain an instance of a subclass of the &apos;&apos;abstract&apos;&apos; `tzinfo` class. (&#x53ef;&#x4ee5;&#x63a1;&#x7528; PyTz &#x63d0;&#x4f9b;&#x7684;&#x5be6;&#x4f5c;)">
<node CREATED="1290663701903" ID="ID_1917714687" MODIFIED="1290663713041" TEXT="These `tzinfo` objects capture information about the offset from &apos;&apos;UTC time&apos;&apos;, the time zone name, and whether Daylight Saving Time is in effect."/>
<node CREATED="1290663713266" ID="ID_1021942619" MODIFIED="1293603819386" TEXT="Note that no concrete `tzinfo` classes are supplied by the `datetime` module. Supporting timezones at whatever level of detail is required is up to the application. The rules for time adjustment across the world are more political than rational, and there is no standard suitable for every application.">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
<icon BUILTIN="messagebox_warning"/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1290664470244" ID="ID_938720998" MODIFIED="1293603464783" TEXT="Objects of these types are &apos;&apos;immutable&apos;&apos;. (&#x56e0;&#x70ba;&#x6240;&#x6709;&#x53ef;&#x80fd;&#x7522;&#x751f;&#x7570;&#x52d5;&#x7684;&#x64cd;&#x4f5c;, &#x90fd;&#x662f;&#x50b3;&#x56de;&#x53e6;&#x4e00;&#x500b; instance)">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
