<node CREATED="1290663930451" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1289833671" MODIFIED="1290663942718" TEXT="tzinfo">
<node CREATED="1290664371588" ID="ID_240783666" MODIFIED="1290664372973" TEXT="Overview">
<node CREATED="1290664373476" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_52988086" MODIFIED="1293612826884" TEXT="An &apos;&apos;abstract base class&apos;&apos;, meaning that this class should not be instantiated directly.">
<node CREATED="1293612827410" ID="ID_38927879" MODIFIED="1293612831719" TEXT="You need to derive a concrete subclass, and (at least) supply implementations of the standard `tzinfo` methods needed by the `datetime` methods you use."/>
<node CREATED="1293612831962" ID="ID_1663399104" MODIFIED="1293612832226" TEXT="The `datetime` module does not supply any concrete subclasses of `tzinfo`."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1290664384921" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1522113838" MODIFIED="1290664407525" TEXT="These are used by the `datetime` and `time` classes to provide a &apos;&apos;customizable notion of time adjustment&apos;&apos; (for example, to account for time zone and/or daylight saving time).">
<node CREATED="1293613089688" ID="ID_1272475077" MODIFIED="1293613119645" TEXT="An instance of (a concrete subclass of) `tzinfo` can be passed to the constructors for `datetime` and `time` objects. The latter objects view their members as being in local time."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1293613122355" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_745541687" MODIFIED="1293616036607" TEXT="The `tzinfo` object supports methods revealing offset of local time from UTC, the name of the time zone, and DST offset, all relative to a date or time object passed to them. (&#x70ba;&#x4ec0;&#x9ebc;&#x8981;&#x50b3;&#x5165; date/time? &#x5be6;&#x9a57;&#x767c;&#x73fe;, &#x50b3;&#x5165; naive date/time, &#x65e5;&#x5b50;&#x6703;&#x597d;&#x904e;&#x4e00;&#x9ede;)">
